This is the "ground • truth" for almost all the content in these slides. As a result, these slides• should be viewed as a presentation of the same content in the professor's • lectures using a different medium. At the same time, these slides are not• meant to be a replacement for the lectures.• The method of incrementally displaying content on slides is borrowed• from professor Mitesh Khapra.• These slides were prepared using the tool mathcha.io.
GMMNotation:• K - number of components• k - index of the kth component• X - r.v for the observation• Z - r.v for the latent variable• 𝜋k - prior probability of the kth component• 𝜇k - mean of the kth component• 𝜎2k - variance of the kth component• fX(x) - density of the GMM• fX,Z(x,z) - joint density of X and Z• fX|Z(x | z) - conditional density of a component• fZ(z) - prior PMF of the latent variable• fZ|X(z | x) - posterior PMF of the latent variable
